---
title: "Disturbing the Memory"
year: 1984
abstract: >
  This is a collection of some weird thoughts, inspired by reading
  "Disturbing the Universe" by Freeman Dyson (1979), reminiscing about
  the history of theoretical physics in the period 1946-1950.
author: ["E.T. Jaynes"]
---

From the first part of Dyson's book we can learn about some incidents of
this important period in the development of theoretical physics, in
which the present writer happened to be a close and interested onlooker
(but, regrettably, not a participant). Dyson's account filled in several
gaps in my own knowledge, and in so doing disturbed my memory into
realizing that I in turn may be in a position to fill in some gaps in
Dyson's account.

